  "NotesEn": "<div>On February 10, 2026, the Senate adopted the following motion:\r\n<p></p>That:\r\n\r\n<p></p>1. the bill be referred to the <a href=\"https://sencanada.ca/en/committees/trcm/45-1\">Standing Senate Committee on Transport and Communications</a>;\r\n\r\n<p></p>2. the <a href=\"https://sencanada.ca/en/committees/lcjc/45-1\">Standing Senate Committee on Legal and Constitutional Affairs</a> be authorized to examine and report on the subject matter of the bill; and\r\n\r\n<p></p>3. the Standing Senate Committee on Transport and Communications be authorized to take into account any report from the Standing Senate Committee on Legal and Constitutional Affairs to the Senate on the subject matter of the bill, during its consideration of the bill.\r\n\r\n</div>",
  "NotesFr": "<div>Le 10 février 2026, le Sénat a adopté la motion suivante : <p></p>Que :\r\n\r\n<p></p>1. le projet de loi soit renvoyé au <a href=\"https://sencanada.ca/fr/comites/trcm/45-1\">Comité sénatorial permanent des transports et des communications</a>;\r\n\r\n<p></p>2. le <a href=\"https://sencanada.ca/fr/comites/lcjc/45-1\">Comité sénatorial permanent des affaires juridiques et constitutionnelles</a> soit autorisé à étudier, afin d’en faire rapport, la teneur du projet de loi;\r\n\r\n<p></p>3. le Comité sénatorial permanent des transports et des communications soit autorisé à prendre en considération tout rapport du Comité sénatorial permanent des affaires juridiques et constitutionnelles déposé au Sénat sur la teneur du projet de loi, au cours de son étude du projet de loi.\r\n\r\n</div>",
  "Notes": "<div>On February 10, 2026, the Senate adopted the following motion:\r\n<p></p>That:\r\n\r\n<p></p>1. the bill be referred to the <a href=\"https://sencanada.ca/en/committees/trcm/45-1\">Standing Senate Committee on Transport and Communications</a>;\r\n\r\n<p></p>2. the <a href=\"https://sencanada.ca/en/committees/lcjc/45-1\">Standing Senate Committee on Legal and Constitutional Affairs</a> be authorized to examine and report on the subject matter of the bill; and\r\n\r\n<p></p>3. the Standing Senate Committee on Transport and Communications be authorized to take into account any report from the Standing Senate Committee on Legal and Constitutional Affairs to the Senate on the subject matter of the bill, during its consideration of the bill.\r\n\r\n</div>",
